The paper deals with visual speech recognition, which involves processing and analyzing visual information (mouth images) to recognize speech. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) domains. The use of LSTM networks for modeling the temporal dynamics of the mouth images suggests a focus on sequential data processing, which is relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also involves experimentation and evaluation of the proposed model, which could be relevant to the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SD).
